Hi Brianna,

Happy to look into this for you! Let me take an initial look into their setup to see what I can verify.

In the meantime, do you think it would be possible to potentially hop on a call with one of their developers and/or team responsible for event tagging in case it might be better to QA in person?

Thanks!

Robbie

Hi Brianna,

Thanks for your patience!

If users submit native forms and close out, later they go on the web, will these users later return to the web as new or existing users?

  • Yes, they will be counted as new users. This is where Click ID will be critical. If a user views the Ad and submits native forms and closes out, Doordash needs to capture the Click ID value for that user. DD will then hang on to that Click ID and tie it to the user on their end
  • When they identify that same user coming back via email address and/or phone number when they log on to web, they would then refer back to that saved Click ID and that would tie that user back to the original session


In my initial investigation it looks like they aren't passing us back a Click ID. Due to the potential disjointed flows, Click ID will be absolutely critical to ensure that the attributions are able to be credited properly: https://business-api.tiktok.com/portal/docs?id=1771100879787009

Would we be able to get them to implement this first and see if this improves their attribution counts?

Thanks!

Robbie

Hey Robbie,


We are working with a few solutions engineers on this account's tracking too, so they would probably be the best people to discuss. Let me ask them about these Click ID issues. I thought we had corrected that element.


Are you able to tell me which event is missing the Click ID? I'm assuming you're talking about Submit Form?


Thank you,

Brianna

Hey Robbie,


Hope you're doing well. Just want to resurface this. I think we're ok on the Click ID, based on responses from our SE team. 


Would you be able to help us confirm the user flow for a new user trying to apply through Dasher's TikTok ads?

We're concerned about the destinations where users land. 


Thank you!

Brianna

Hi Brianna,

Sorry for the delay here! I ran another query and it looks like Click ID is still not being captured. We do have Click ID entries available but they are only for those page visits through an Instant Page and the in-app browser. The Click ID is automatically populated but it is up to the advertiser to grab that value and pass it through with each subsequent server side event.

And yes, I will go ahead and test the new Dasher flow. Will I have to complete the entire process? I am unfortunately not looking for a second job at the moment :) Is there any available documentation outlining the intended flow?

Thanks!

Robbie

Hey Robbie,


I'll attach screenshots of Kai and Braden's conversation about click ID for these events. They seemed to arrive at the conclusion that this is acceptable. If you disagree with the logic still, please let me know! And I'll relay to them. 



Hahah, that's how I've felt while testing it too, but please feel free to use dummy names and email addresses!

What we're specifically looking to see is after you've filled out the native lead form, which webpage or app page you're brought to, and after completing that form, where does it bring you. Please do not enter any information for the background check process. 

The documented process on their website is as follows: https://help.doordash.com/dashers/s/article/Dasher-Signup-Process?language=en_US 

However, we know that they've already moved the background check process to app, and we've seen mixed results on our end whether the DoorDash-hosted form is on web or app. 



Thanks for all of your help!!!

Brianna

Hey Robbie,


Have you been able to check out my reply?


Thank you!

Brianna

Hi Brianna,

Apologies! I have been on PTO since Thursday last week but I'll make sure to address this as soon as I can.

Thanks!

Robbie

Oh shoot! Sorry, Robbie! Welcome back.


Thanks for your help!

Hi Brianna,

Thanks so much for your patience here!

I was able to try out the new driver flow and it looks like the website only goes as far as gathering an Email address and a phone number, ending in this screen:

Then when I head over to the Dasher app to continue the application, it asks for this same information when you select the "Sign up to Dash" and "Already started signing up?" button - email address and phone number.

Within the app, the background check process is then loaded into a Webview in the app itself.

I think I may have found our culprit here - it seems like a fair amount of Submit Form events are coming in without an Email address:

Here are a sampling of URLs without hashed PII

  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-au?source=dx_signup_cx_ios&internal-referrer=legacy-signup
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-us?utm_platform=ios&utm_source=sms&internal-referrer=legacy-signup&referrer_id=22234991&referral_campaign_id=282782
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-au?utm_source=google-sem-brand&utm_medium=semb&utm_campaign=dx_au_se_sb_go_acq_cauxxx_13954459593_%2Bbr_acq_xxxxx_catchxxxxxxxx_evg_cpax_epx_coaus_en_en_x_dash_go_se_txt_catchallxx&utm_term=drive%20with%20doordash&utm_content=694026765837_._EAIaIQobChMI3anjv4yChQMVhGwPAh1m-Q1kEAAYASAAEgLSb_D_BwE&kclickid=_k_EAIaIQobChMI3anjv4yChQMVhGwPAh1m-Q1kEAAYASAAEgLSb_D_BwE_k_&utm_id=go_cmp-13954459593_adg-154990218148_ad-694026765837_kwd-781817134982_dev-m_ext-_prd-_mca-_sig-EAIaIQobChMI3anjv4yChQMVhGwPAh1m-Q1kEAAYASAAEgLSb_D_BwE&gad_source=1&gbraid=0AAAAADACs0RWvhr8c8PTpG9ol6d_XRzIv&gclid=EAIaIQobChMI3anjv4yChQMVhGwPAh1m-Q1kEAAYASAAEgLSb_D_BwE
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-us


Interestingly, we also see that these same URLs will receive hashed PII as well:

  • https://dasher.doordash.com/es-us?source=dx_app_iOS
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/fr-ca?source=apply_android&intl=fr-CA
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-us?campaign=dundee-mi&rx_c=amp_1710347218563&rx_campaign=Indeed1&rx_ch=jobp4p&rx_group=349201&rx_job=notier-dddnen-dundee-mi-48131-20240201&rx_medium=cpc&rx_r=none&rx_source=Indeed&rx_ts=20240320T000541Z&rx_vp=cpc&utm_campaign=dx_us_jb_rc_re_acq_5768xx_11111_%2B_Dundee%2C%20MI_5768&utm_content=recruitics&utm_medium=indeed&utm_source=recruitics&rx_p=CWN8ZSC4VF&rx_viewer=a70ea152b3f411eeb187f1d296e6b63010098fe347d34240a6941cead7264799
  • https://dasher.doordash.com/en-us?utm_source=Kepler-TikTok&utm_medium=TikTok_Lead_Acquisition&utm_campaign=dx_us_ps_tt_tk_acq_d517xx_11111_%2B&utm_term=charlotte&utm_content=TikTokLeadForm&ttclid=E_C_P_CsoBDssFBvS-h4zltSnbO0lH355q_KUU1SyVVqEK5h93PtdDwu78W1lUae2RLYpCFqJeCeHFqckDfbYN_PH3jzekOZGSLIYPsZPQ8F9J2I6zzuRVm_VZ9GkHzpvBCXPD3dgK2An5x3U-S6wNzqjzcSZ_8ADzwCXPO5b1pQp53XrXGqRhEG7mvbJvxpgHXuI184F-xlBDA6-YeJn-b99FtjeXuYaDZ9xnro0LQO3iirKv0yMqDcSE7Cf7vQtPF58AwotqfyXyrqYJ6CmSNRIEdjIuMBogABIFgULiRmDPCStM_PNSORTa57T17AjMnoTW1zmH8P8&is_from_prerender=0


I would assume this may be in part of new privacy implementations in iOS and Android platforms, but it would also be worth having the DoorDash team look into this as it is difficult for us to debug and look into the network calls from within Mobile apps. I've attached a CSV output of SubmitForm events for 3/20 that may help with an investigation on their end.

Thanks and I really appreciate your patience here!

Best,

Robbie

Hi Robbie,

Thank you for the thorough investigation! Jumping in here as Bri is OOO for the rest of the week. I am the Measurement Partner on the account and have been closely involved in the process.

To clarify, re: user flow, can you confirm that my understanding is correct? After filling out Instant Form on TikTok, you then was directed to the Dasher website and was able to go through filling Email and Phone information on web before being prompted with "Time to download.." screen. If so, this should be the flow we expect as we believe Form web event fires after users successfully input email and phone.

Re: email missing from Form event. Confirming the data you showed here are from 3/20. Our SE POC was able to confirm 100% coverage for email with 100% formatting accuracy a few days ago. Does this mean certain PIIs fall off in the last few days? and/or may be related to the new privacy implementation on IOS and Android you mentioned? Is it missing at a large scale that we should be worried? Should we reach out to SE to triple check again?

Thanks again for your help, Robbie!

Kat

Hi Kat!

Regarding the user flow, that is correct:

  • Enter Name, Phone number, and zipcode, the Email address is automatically populated 
  • Thanks for your response! page appears - user is invited to click on the "Click to continue sign up" button
  • Then from within the in app browser, the dasher.doordash.com page is loaded and the user continues to sign up and is eventually directed to download the Dasher app

That is interesting! They may be seeing something I am not but I would definitely go back and have SE to check again based off of the data from 3/20 in the CSV file I provided yesterday - highlighting these specifically:

  • PixelAdLog means that the data came onsite, from the Instant Form on the TT app
  • Presence of a Click ID and an ad_id value also validates the user came from the Instant Form
  • However, if we look at the Email and Phone columns, some are empty
  • Note regarding the query is that it was ran with a limit of 10000 rows

The assumption is that every Instant Form submission would have a hashed email and/or phone number tied with it as it is coming from the TT app.

Thanks!

Robbie

Hi Robbie,

Thank you so much for the quick follow-up and the detailed call outs. Sounds good on user flow! I have reached out to  SE to investigate further regarding missing emails/phones and the information you provide will certainly be helpful.

It is indeed interesting especially for Instant Form, we would expect Instant Form to capture email and phone, right? Email is auto-filled already. Does this imply the instant form is not working properly or mean users just did not fill out the instant form but somehow bypassed and trigged the event? 

Thanks,

Kat

Hi Kat,

I've previewed the Ad a few times and tried to input invalid values and it would not let me proceed to submit the instant form. If we take a closer look at the data and drill down - we can see that the Instant Form submission events with null PII are coming from iPhone/iOS devices:

It's hard to say specifically what might be causing this, but if I were to hazard a guess of any kind (I would not put any money on this by any means), these may be from users that have declined the ATT prompt for the TikTok app. The App Transparency Tracking prompt explicitly mentions tracking across other apps and websites but I'm not sure if it prevents the outgoing webview traffic from within the app potentially containing PII. I will do some further research on this

If we look at it from the mobile app, event tracking SKAD network perspective, it would make some sense since event data becomes aggregated and we lose granularity when it comes to parameters. Almost everything ends up being obfuscated and translated into Conversion Values.

I will run another query that will pull all SubmitForm events for 3/20 and see if this hypothesis still stands up if it is exclusively only for iOS users.

Thanks!

Robbie

Hi Kat - it does look like it is only occurring for iOS users. I've attached an updated CSV file showing all SubmitForm events for 3/20

Out of 24693 tracked SubmitForm events for 3/20

  • 72 submitted through the Instant Form
  • 28 with NULL values for email/phone and all through iPhone/iOS devices
  • For non-instant form SubmitForm events, 214 have come in with NULL values with email/phone
    • These have all come in through the user agent 'UA-name:iOSDasherWebView (iPhone); client-version: 2.315.0.82904' which I would assume indicates that these are applications submitted through the iOS Dasher app

Thanks!

Robbie

Hi Robbie,

Thank you for the insights! This is very clear and helpful. Excellent investigation. You are right that certain browsers may face tracking limitations with IOS devices. I will get more information on this as well. 

To understand the scale of null PIIs and gauge the implications, I did some simple filtering and calculations based on the file. Can you confirm this is in line with your understanding? Out of ~25K tracked SubmitForm web events, ~63% events were from OS devices and among those, 5% of events return null PIIs. Overall, we have ~3% PIIs missing. 

Thanks,
Kat

Hi Kat,

Yes those numbers do align with what I am seeing as well. Not necessarily a large amount but is definitely worth looking into.

Referring back to the original question, would you happen to have any Campaigns and/or Ad Group IDs that are using the native forms where we're not seeing attributions for?

Thanks!

Robbie

Hey Robbie,


Here's an ad group example for lead gen with no Submit Forms: 1766275401054209


Thank you!

Bri

Hi Brianna,

Thanks for the example! It looks like historically they were never able to attribute any of their Submit Form events to their campaigns. Taking a look at the timeframe from 2023-07-01 to 2024-03-27, Lead conversions in the app were captured but the Submit Form pixel events themselves never got attributed 

This is interesting because in the data that I provided a few messages ago for all SubmitForm events on 3/20, there were Submit Form events that were tied to an Ad Group and did have hashed PII sent along with them and Click IDs present for the instant form events.

At this point it does feel like this could be a potential UI bug. Was this possibility discussed with the SEs?

Thanks!

Robbie

items.label: Detailed Description
items.content:
1. We need help finding out the exact user flow (full loop) from App native form to Web and stress testing different scenarios. 
a. If users submit native forms and close out, later they go on the web, will these users later return to the web as new or existing users? This impacts measurement largely as it dictates different user experience. 
b. If users go through the flow (from native to web) in one session, what events are being fired? 
c. If users do not submit on native form but later come back on the web, what events are fired? 

2. We suspect that Instant Form overwrites Web form attribution but needs confirmation and solution so we can inform any optimization needed and corresponding measurement.

items.label: Reason for request: Please briefly describe the help needed for this account.
items.content:
We're working through some troubleshooting/problem-solving after a conversion lift study that we ran for the DoorDash Dasher account. They run primarily lead generation (native form) campaigns, and we've noticed that the submit form web event does not attribute to these campaigns. However, that's the primary KPI that they want to track in their conversion lift studies.

We're asking for MPO assistance because we need help validating the user flow and the events that are triggered when a TikTok user tries to sign up to become a Dasher. 

In our own attempts, we've experienced a variety of redirections to app and continuations to different webpages, so we're looking for your help to strategically test the userflow and validate the pathway for a user to convert. This will allow us to confidently run another CLS for the client. 

We were advised to submit this ticket by our MarSci partner.
